b"[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](sbe48559.htm)  [Next](sbe48561.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n9\\. And for this very reason without another ruler.\n\nSince the released soul realises all its wishes, it does not stand under\nanother ruler. For to be under a ruler means to be subject to injunction and\nprohibition, and to be such is opposed to being free in the realisation of all\none's wishes. Hence Scripture says, 'he is a Self-ruler' ( _Kh_. Up. VII, 25).\n--Here terminates the adhikara _n_ a of 'wishes.'\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: 10. The absence...](sbe48561.htm)\n\n"